column5: Is that what the black blob is? too funny
I think I am going to Cancel my cable this is much more exciting even my wife who cares less about fishing is watching it lol.
This cam is awesome!!!! In 20 minutes I have seen about 10 suckers, somekind of newt or salamander and 2 huge sturgeon!!!!!!!

Something bonked the camera and at the moment it is pointing down-current so the fish are approaching the camera head-on. Personally, I think it's less effective for identification and sizing that way.  Wolf River Cam  --
That camera is a good watch!  If you look real close there is consistently something real big hanging out in the background (4:55).  It has appeared 3 or 4 times.
It came in close for a bit. Twas a Sturgeon
I saw a pair of reading glasses tumble by. SKEETER ????
Suckers, walleye, carp, sturgeon was in and out for quiet some time and a whitefish. All in about 10 minutes.
Busy night. One camera appears to be turned around and I think the sturgeon getting frisky with one of the others.
This camera has strurgeon spawning right now:  http://wolfrivercam.com/Shiocton%20Cam%202.html
would running this all the time kill your allotted download quota from your ISP ?
There must be 6 Sturgeon kickin up silt right now////  19:37pm VERY VERY COOL!!!  Randy from STURGEON
That's not silt, but it does rhyme with it.
I think that Camera #2 is now pregnant.

It isn't as interesting as the eagle nest cam because sometimes you only see water, but there's an underwater river cam here: Wolf River cam  I watched the odd sucker swim by while I was watching, but a few minutes ago a huge sturgeon swam right by the camera!   --
That's pretty cool I just watched it for a few mins and seen a walleye, sucker and a big Sheap head, I could watch this all night lol.
There is lots of action right now check it out.
Now that is cool...
That Sturgeon likes to kick up the silt...

I saw that too. I also notice that it's getting harder to see fish outside the range of the light of the camera now that darkness is settling in. There seems to be quite a variety of species in that river.   --
so far I've got a Sturgeon , a bunch of Walleye ,, some Sucker and a Smallie
Yea I can't stop watching, this is awesome lol. It's exciting just waiting to see what's next lol.
Pretty cool indeed.  That sturgeon is great
Awesome, I think I saw debris, couldn't make it out. I'm going to watch this just to see what happens.
Did anyone see that big sturgeon with the lamprey attached a few minutes ago? That was pretty hideous looking.  --
been watching an hour..not a damn thing....LOL

Some observations: - As Terry noted, this time of day seems to have less fish traffic than later in the afternoon and just before dusk yesterday (just like fishing). - Species seen so far: Sturgeon, Walleye, Sucker, Smallmouth Bass, Sheepshead, Lamprey, Carp (any others?) - A snail decided to clean the camera and blocked most of the view for a while earlier this morning LOL.
I think that there was a Small Pike or Chain Pickerel sitting there at about 5:30 this morning.
I saw carp  then sucker  then walleye
Me too and a Sturgeon!
i seen them too...who needs a fish tank eh ....  i think im going to keep this going all the time to act as a screen saver...  nice find!!!  Cheers
Another species sighted: Johnny Darter (although I don't expect the poor little guy to last long among some of those predators)  --

I saw a big Sturgeon swimming into the current and crayfish that seemed like he walked out from under the camera! Also just saw something that looked like a whitefish, couldn't tell they flew through the screen but were big.
Two weeks ago it was a steady stream of walleye one after the other,lots of suckers and one sturgeon.

will this work? YES!!
Live video chat by Ustream
No watching the river cam while you're driving though, okay Randy?
This link has been posted here the last 3 or 4 springs, but this is the first time I remember seeing sturgeon.
Damn snail is back
It's movin', but at a snails pace.
